      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:41:6",
      "text": [
        " لَوْ أَنَّ رَجُلًا حَفَرَ بِئْراً فِي دَارِهِ ثُمَّ دَخَلَ رَجُلٌ فَوَقَعَ فِيهَا لَمْ يَكُنْ عَلَيْهِ شَيْ‏ءٌ وَ لَا ضَمَانٌ وَ لَكِنْ لِيُغَطِّهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Sahl and Ibn Abu Najran, both together from Ibn Abu Nasr, from Musanna Al Hannat, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘If a man were to dig a well in his house, then a man enters and falls into it, there is nothing upon him, and no responsibility, but for covering it’."
        ]
      }
    },
